  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "arM+mrmaiHtLuDweU7TwPYUb2mc=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:33.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Dual-push: personal feed plus collab feed\n\nFor a drive/doc that is part of a collaboration, the user's reactor still produces ops locally. Those ops need to flow to two places:\n\n- **Their personal drive feeds** \u2014 unchanged. Still wallet-key encrypted. This keeps the user's cross-device recovery working without any migration.\n- **Their collab feeds** \u2014 ACT-protected, so peers can read them.\n\n### Implementation\n\nSwarmChannel gains a `collabTargets` set. For each ordinal it would push to the personal feed, it *also* pushes to the collab feed if the doc is in an active collab. **One read of the op, two pushes.** The second upload reuses the same op-batch payload with `{ act: true }`.\n\n### Why not push-only to the collab feed\n\nDual-push preserves the existing cross-device recovery story: if the user only had the collab-feed copy, losing the collab (or being removed from it) would orphan their own history on that device. The personal feed is their source of truth; the collab feed is the per-collab projection.\n\n### Future optimization\n\nFor docs that exist *only* inside a collab \u2014 e.g., a doc imported via collab accept and never independently owned \u2014 the personal-feed push could be skipped entirely. Out of scope for v1.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:33.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:33.000Z"
    }
  },
